    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - CATERPILLAR
        3176B/3406E ELECTRONIC ENGINE CONTROLS - 1994 - WELDING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WELDING</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Disconnect the positive (+) and negative (-) battery cables from the battery before welding on the
                    vehicle. Attach the welder ground cable as close as possible to the part being welded. Do not
                    connect the welder ground cable to any part of the ECM or ECM mounting bracket. Remove all
                    connections from the ECM before welding.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
